value.name: Black Lantern Corps - Wikipedia
value.snippet: The Black Lantern Corps is a fictional organization of corporeal revenants (resembling intelligent zombies or jiangshi) appearing in comic books published by DC Comics, related to the emotional spectrum. The group is composed of deceased fictional characters in zombie form that seek to eliminate all life from the DC Universe .

value.name: Black Lantern Corps (New Earth) | DC Database | Fandom
value.snippet: The Black Lantern Corps are the slain and deceased beings from throughout the universe who fell into the domain of the dead. They are the army of Nekron, the Lord of the Unliving, and their purpose is to eliminate all life. The Black Lantern Rings are wielded by the deceased.

value.name: Black Lantern Corps (disambiguation) | DC Database | Fandom
value.snippet: The Black Lantern Corps is one of the ten Lantern Corps that draw power from the Emotional Electromagnetic Spectrum. The original was the Green Lantern Corps, and the Black Lanterns have been enemies to the super-hero Green Lantern. The Black Lanterns are fueled by death. value.name: Black Lanterns: How Does DC's DEADLIEST Corps Work? - CBR
value.snippet: The Black Lanterns are reanimated corpses brought to life by rings created by Nekron, a being who is seen as the living embodiment of death. Within the scriptures of Oa, it is foretold that one day, the Blackest Night shall descend upon the universe, causing the end of all things, and Nekron uses the Black Lanterns to do just this in Geoff Johns and Ivan Reis' Blackest Night event.

value.name: Every Kind Of DC Lantern Corps, Ranked - CBR
value.snippet: The most terrifying of the Lantern Corps, the Black Lanterns are powered by the very edge of the emotional spectrum, death. A human named William Hand created the Corps during the events of Blackest Night. Black Hand, as he became known, used the power of Nekron, the entity of death, to raise an entire army of the dead. Notable Members: Black Hand

value.name: Black Lantern Corps | Villains Wiki | Fandom
value.snippet: The Black Lantern Corps are a major antagonistic organization from DC comics that are part of the Blackest Night crossover series - they are the reanimated corpses of deceased former DC heroes and villains returned to life with a black power ring and with the sole purpose of eradicating all living life in the DC universe on behalf of their god-like master, Nekron.

value.name: Black Lantern Corps (History) - Comic Basics
value.snippet: Name: Black Lantern Corps. Founding Members: Black Hand. First Appearance: Green Lantern Volume 4, #25 (January, 2008) Created By: Geoff Johns, Ian Reiss, Ethan Van Scriver. Did You Know: Many well-known heroes have served as members of the Black Lantern Corps. A Little History. Along with creating many other Lantern groups, Geoff Johns was the chief architect of the Black Lanterns.
